  <heading>FMMLA (non-widening)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Half-precision matrix multiply-accumulate</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction multiplies the 2x2 matrix of half-precision values
in each 64-bit segment of the first source vector by the 2x2 matrix
of half-precision values in the corresponding 64-bit segment
of the second source vector. The intermediate products
are rounded before they are summed, and the intermediate sum is rounded
before accumulation into the 2x2 half-precision matrix held in the corresponding
64-bit segment of the addend and destination vector.
This is equivalent to performing a 2-way dot product per destination element.</para>
    </authored>
  </desc>
